		<h1>Getting Started</h1>
		The first step would be to <a href="https://scratch.mit.edu/projects/editor/">create Scratch projects</a>(or pick pre-existing ones). If you don't have a Scratch account, then you should make one, and create some projects.
		<h2>Ideas for Clutters</h2>
		Here are some ideas for clutters.
		<ul>
			<li><h3>Create a Story</h3>
			Create a story or comic book series, and combine them on Clutter.</li>
			<li><h3>Make a Game Series</h3>
			Compile your game series into a single place!</li>
			<li><h3>Make a Show</h3>
			Create edisodes of a show, and make a easy to find place for all of them.</li>
			<li><h3>Create an Art Gallery</h3>
			Take your art, and put it into a gallery, for everyone to enjoy.</li>
			<li><h3>Create a compilation album</h3>
			Show of you're own original music, or music you just generally like.</li>
			<li><h3>Compile your favorite projects</h3>
			Make an easy place to access your personal favorite projects by you.</li>
			<li><h3>Create a Clutter of similar projects</h3>
			Add a bunch of projects similar in style, tone, ideas, or any other way.</li>
			<li><h3>Index all your most popular projects</h3>
			Put you're most popular projects to a Clutter</li>
		</ul>
		<h2>Still don't know what to make?</h2>
		I bet you can come up with your own ideas! You really don't need this, but it may give you ideas to base what you may want to make off of.
